dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Chepstow, solid and drift, sheet 250
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 250 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 51.700000. South Decimal Degree 51.5333. East Decimal Degree -2.4833. West Decimal Degree -2.9167. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain (seventh series). Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depth shown by contour intervals. "Original geological survey published on Old Series Sheet 35 in 1845, revised 1866 & 1872. Survey on the six-inch scale in 1937-39 by F. B. A. Welch et al. Additional information 1953-55 by F. B. A. Welch, et al.".
